 Likewise, 4K upscaling isn&#39;t a perfect substitute for content recorded in 4K, but it&#39;s a similarly useful way to take advantage of a 4K HDTV when you don&#39;t purchase 4K Blu-ray discs. Upscaled DVDs had crisp pictures, with deep blacks and vibrant colors.","We timed how long it took each player to reach its home menu on stock settings, and the S6500 took a respectable 11.3 seconds. This is in line with comparable Blu-ray players, which had an average boot time of 12 seconds."]},"id":"d54404d1-4993-4508-89e5-5470b39f6666","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Connectivity &amp; Design"},"id":"dcb4699d-d17b-4982-8572-9394bb9805f8","type":"heading"},{"data":{"path":"/FJYWANw2yQBaC7Pm6tkTwU.jpg","link":{"href":"","rel":null,"target":""},"caption":"The Blu-ray player has a nice compact body, but it would be better if Sony made the case with metal instead of plastic. Its dimensions are 10 x 7.6 x 1.5 inches, and it weighs only 2 pounds. There are two buttons on the face of the player: one for power and the other to open and close the disk tray.","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/69011-sony4.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/FJYWANw2yQBaC7Pm6tkTwU.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"FJYWANw2yQBaC7Pm6tkTwU","mos":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/FJYWANw2yQBaC7Pm6tkTwU.jpg","alt":""},"id":"765e60b6-cde8-4683-b85a-85848ebe7e04","type":"image"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["This Sony has plenty of connectivity options, including both Wi-Fi support and an Ethernet jack. On its front side, underneath the power button, there is a single USB port you can plug an external hard drive into to play your stored video and photo files. You can also download a mobile app on your smartphone that lets you use it as a remote control. The included remote, however, is small but operable in the dark. It even has a shortcut for Netflix.","Besides Netflix, the BDP-S6500 has preloaded apps for Facebook, YouTube, BBC iPlayer, PlayStation Video and a few other services. These apps, among others, are easy to find and access, but they don’t load extremely fast. The layout of the home screen is logical and the interface is easy to use, though."]},"id":"3faef345-4b12-49b1-93a5-33f96a905554","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Audio"},"id":"d70d7eee-dd45-4174-b408-9bc32bef442f","type":"heading"},{"data":{"path":"/WnQfeFJJf3oqoUaamDP3FA.jpg","link":{"href":"","rel":null,"target":""},"caption":"This Blu-ray player is DLNA compatible, so you can upload your music and video to the cloud and access the files wirelessly. It also supports Dolby True HD and DTS HD Master Audio, so you can use an AV receiver or a sound bar for surround sound.","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/69011-sony8.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/WnQfeFJJf3oqoUaamDP3FA.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"WnQfeFJJf3oqoUaamDP3FA","mos":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/WnQfeFJJf3oqoUaamDP3FA.jpg","alt":""},"id":"fac2c729-cb36-475e-9d75-6ec0ce2c8b32","type":"image"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The back panel has coaxial audio outputs, which should suffice for most people. Most mainstream Blu-ray players feature either coaxial or optical output. Your home audio equipment will usually have one or the other. However, audiophiles may want a second HDMI audio output, which this one doesn’t have."]},"id":"5e7b5eae-f2cc-48a5-9749-52c909859da4","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Help &amp; Support"},"id":"d0f8966c-ab60-4312-a38a-7d4ec6738618","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Sony includes a one-year warranty with its S6500 Blu-ray player. The company also offers support through several channels, including phone, email, live chat and information on its website. Online, you can find a FAQs page, troubleshooting guides and a downloadable manual."]},"id":"1d58e86a-2eb9-4d24-bee6-2be27c14d3ea","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"a7088566-3135-4b58-ab8f-28f4c2955e01","type":"heading"},{"data":{"para